Following a general pediatric residency, physicians can pursue fellowships in specific subspecialties: 

Neonatology: Care for newborns, especially premature or critically ill infants.

Pediatric cardiology: Diagnosis and treatment of heart conditions in children.

Pediatric oncology: Specializes in childhood cancers.

Pediatric infectious disease: Management of serious infections.

Developmental-behavioral pediatrics: Focuses on developmental disorders and behavioral issues.

Adolescent medicine: Addresses the unique health needs of teenagers. 
